    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p>My dear sir</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName> <date>Jany 31.&#39;54</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You were good enough to loan<lb/> me some years ago &#8220;The Chronicles of<lb/> <persName>Rabbi Joseph Ben Joshua Ben Meir</persName>&#44; the<lb/> Sph<add>&#63;</add>&#8221;&#8212;translated by <persName>Bialloblotzky<add>&#63;</add></persName>&#8212;<lb/> I have lately added to my little collection<lb/> of Hebrew matter a copy of the Original<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> and would like again to have<lb/> for a while your vols&#58; if you will do me<lb/> that favour I shall be obliged to you&#8212;</p>
			<p>We have been expecting for some time<lb/> our copy of your Bible&#44; as we understand<lb/> that it was in the hands of <persName><add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> in <placeName>Phila</placeName> <persName>Dr McCulloh</persName> has been long<lb/> anxious for his&#8212;and <persName>Mr Lenaman</persName> also<lb/> wishes a copy&#8212;so that when our turn<lb/> comes</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><add>&#63;</add> be supplied.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Adams Express will be a convenient<lb/> means of sending me the vols.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I am truly<add>&#63;</add> your friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Joshua I. Cohen</persName></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
